 The unit of the answer should be  .
Solution: I need to find the probability that the maximum number of successes among three drugs exceeds 8, when each drug is tested on 10 patients with success probability p = 0.7.

**Setup:**
- 3 drugs, each tested on n = 10 patients
- Each patient is randomly assigned one drug
- Success probability for each drug: p₁ = p₂ = p₃ = 0.7
- Find: P(max(X₁, X₂, X₃) > 8) where Xᵢ ~ Binomial(10, 0.7)

**Solution:**

Since each drug is tested independently on 10 patients, each Xᵢ follows a Binomial(10, 0.7) distribution.

P(max(X₁, X₂, X₃) > 8) = P(at least one drug has > 8 successes)
                        = 1 - P(all three drugs have ≤ 8 successes)
                        = 1 - [P(X ≤ 8)]³

where X ~ Binomial(10, 0.7).

**Calculate P(X ≤ 8):**

P(X ≤ 8) = 1 - P(X ≥ 9) = 1 - [P(X = 9) + P(X = 10)]

For Binomial(10, 0.7):

P(X = 9) = C(10,9) × (0.7)⁹ × (0.3)¹
         = 10 × 0.040353607 × 0.3
         = 0.121060821

P(X = 10) = C(10,10) × (0.7)¹⁰ × (0.3)⁰
          = 1 × 0.028247553 × 1
          = 0.028247553

P(X ≥ 9) = 0.121060821 + 0.028247553 = 0.149308374

P(X ≤ 8) = 1 - 0.149308374 = 0.850691626

**Calculate the final probability:**

P(max > 8) = 1 - [P(X ≤ 8)]³
           = 1 - (0.850691626)³
           = 1 - 0.614909829
           = 0.385090171

